The paper deals with the problem of dictionary matching, which is a classic problem in string matching. This problem is related to data structures and algorithms for efficient text processing, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the space occupancy of the Aho-Corasick automaton, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a new data structure for dictionary matching, which is related to data mining (cs.DM).
